public class WeightedSnapshotTreeModelImpl
extends java.lang.Object
implements de.engehausen.treemap.IWeightedTreeModel<ISnapshotNode>, de.engehausen.treemap.ILabelProvider<ISnapshotNode>, ISnapshotProvider

Result tree model (a weighted tree model implementation). To become fully initialized, the initialize(IProgressListener) method must be called after the model creation.

The method initialize(IProgressListener) computes the weighted tree model by traversing the graph of the snapshot nodes as formed by its GC root nodes, turning it into a tree and assigning the accumulated weight of its individual nodes accordingly. This may be a naive approach and the built tree is just one of many possible trees that could be formed from the graph. It will not be safe to conclude certain containments just from the tree map; the tree map of the heap can just give an idea of the object distribution and size. "Normal" analysis of the heap will be required to fully understand the object reference situation in the heap and how to possibly reduce the heap size.

This tree model is not thread-safe.
